<TITLE> Bus fares reset on diesel price cut </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com) The government has reset maximum fares of diesel-run buses and minibuses, effective from Sunday midnight. The fares have been lowered on the back of cuts in fuel prices, said a press information department handout. Fares will come down to 98 paisa per kilometre from Tk 1.50 for buses, except those plying through Mawa and Paturia by ferry, which will come down to Tk 1.01 from Tk 1.08 per km. Fares will also be reduced to Tk 1.04 from Tk 1.11 per km for mini-buses en route to Mawa and Paturia by ferries. bd
